1
00:00:06,880 --> 00:00:09,720
What’s this? Look at all the police cars!
-Good thing they're going the other way.

2
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:11,800
What’s good? They’re headed towards my parents' place.

3
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:13,920
The good thing is we’re not going to your parents'.

4
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:16,040
There’s no traffic towards my parents'.
-Really.

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,400
Well, who knows, maybe it’s some
police conference or "Police Day."

6
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:22,680
Friday night? What, are they doing Kiddush?

7
00:00:22,840 --> 00:00:28,320
"On the sixth day, the heavens
and the earth and all their hosts..."

8
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:30,480
Who knows, maybe something happened, God forbid.

9
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:32,439
Ron.
Bar
!m
.Room.
n
ROVl M 'bo'

10
00:00:33,080 --> 00:00:35,560
Did you know my dream used to be to be a cop?
-Really.

11
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:39,120
I even learned Krav Maga
to disarm someone with a gun.

12
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:42,120
Sounds like a nightmare to me.
-Why?

13
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:44,800
The police have come a long way
since the days of Officer Azulai.

14
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,440
I don’t know why. I can’t picture you

15
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:48,120
in a police uniform. It’s funny.

16
00:00:48,480 --> 00:00:51,640
I think if you were in the police,
they’d give you your own district,

17
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:53,800
District Sh'.
-Very funny.

18
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,440
Soon I’ll stop you for insulting a public servant.

19
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:58,440
What, I insulted you, babe?
-Just a little, yeah.

20
00:00:58,920 --> 00:01:02,200
You can get out of the car
since all the streets are empty now,

21
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:05,560
the alleys are all yours.

22
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,480
He’s running over there.

23
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:24,960
Did you see anything?
-"Lighter," here "cigarette,"

24
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:27,160
"Lighter," here "cigarette."
We urgently need fire.

25
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:29,320
I repeat: we urgently need fire.

26
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:34,360
Wow, what tension.
-What nonsense.

27
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:37,160
Things like this only happen on TV.
-No, it’s not nonsense,

28
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:39,080
it happens in real life too. Read the papers.

29
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:48,440
Tell me, those shows,
are they based on reality or TV?

30
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:51,320
It’s really intense.
-What do you mean?

31
00:01:51,440 --> 00:01:53,360
What’s this? Who are you?
-Don’t move!

32
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:54,720
No, you see I’m not.
-Quiet.

33
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,160
Be careful.

34
00:01:57,800 --> 00:02:00,360
Leave him alone!
-Quiet! Sit down.

35
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:03,960
What are you, a thief?
-No, I’m not a thief.

36
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:06,640
Quiet. I don’t want to hear a word.

37
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,280
Any suspicious move from you,
I’ll blow everything up. Got it?

38
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,080
Be careful, I’m telling you, be careful, I’m warning you.

39
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:17,160
I’m sure everything’s fine.
-Yeah. Sure.

40
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:19,320
What are the odds this is related to my mom?
-Exactly.

41
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:26,360
Look at me, look at me and...

42
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:40,600
Sali, do something.
-What do you want me to do?

43
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,760
He said quiet so...

44
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,160
I don’t need help, thank you very much. Quiet now.

45
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:47,320
Mr. Thief, do me a favor, take whatever you want,

46
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,480
just let us go. Look, it’s time.

47
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,720
First of all, I told you, I’m not a thief.

48
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:56,720
I wasn’t focused.

49
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,960
I’m between jobs right now.
-Ah, right.

50
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:02,360
Now be quiet. If you listen to me,
everything will be fine.

51
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:05,200
How will it be fine? It sounds
like all of Israel's police are down there

52
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:07,440
!Interpol too! And the FBI...

53
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,640
You want him to blow us up?

54
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:13,040
The instructions are as follows: if the police come in here,

55
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:16,160
you don’t give me up at any cost. Got it?
-Got it.

56
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:19,840
For you, I’m part of the family.
Then everything will be fine.

57
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:22,840
But if one of you sings...
-No way...

58
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:24,280
I’ll blow everything up. Is that clear?

59
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,360
Clear.
-Clear.

60
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:29,280
Great. I’m glad you accepted me into your family.

61
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,320
Well, you don't choose your family.

62
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,920
Shh...
-What shh?

63
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:36,760
What, are we just going to sit here and wait for the police to arrive?

64
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,160
We can have dinner.

65
00:03:40,640 --> 00:03:44,920
Mr. Gabb... uh... between jobs.

66
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,680
Excuse me, hello.

67
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:51,360
It's Friday night. I really, really would like

68
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,840
to make Kiddush for Shabbat.

69
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,320
Hands up! You're surrounded!

70
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:58,240
What is that? Who is it?
-Not that... sorry, TV.

71
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:04,160
What's going on? Why do they always say to come
early and then everyone is late?

72
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:07,360
That's Shai. He never shows up late.

73
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:10,920
Come on, really, Rivka.
-Shai wouldn't leave me alone like this.

74
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:13,160
Rivka, you're not alone.
-Okay, I need to go,

75
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,080
so if they're not coming, I'm eating and leaving.

76
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:18,959
Adam, you're not a street kid. Even when there's a meal,

77
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:23,040
the whole family sits together and eats.
-Let him eat and go.

78
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:25,280
Maybe he's in a hurry?
-Shabbat Shalom!

79
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:27,600
Oh, Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

80
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:30,200
Already creating a fuss. Where have you been?
-No, everything's fine, everything's fine.

81
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:33,480
We're sorry for being late.
There were just so many police and checkpoints.

82
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:37,080
Okay, let's eat. Adam's in a hurry.
He has to leave the house.

83
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:40,640
Hurry or he'll lose his mind.
-What's the rush?

84
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,680
On Fridays, there are only flowers in the streets.

85
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,680
I'm going to tidy up.
-What's the rush?

86
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:49,200
I was invited to dinner.
-The pretty one...

87
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:52,920
Someone's parents.
-Since when do you go to someone's parents?

88
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,400
Forget it, bro, we're talking about a family
sitting on so much money

89
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,720
that sometimes Shari Arison babysits for them.

90
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:01,240
Wow...

91
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,320
Get a grip.

92
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:09,960
Good morning. There's so much police outside. Did you see?

93
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,280
Why didn't you tell me there was someone here?

94
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:16,320
Hey, who are you?
-He's the reason all the police are downstairs.

95
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,560
What do you mean? What's going on?
-This is Merav, our daughter.

96
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:22,400
She lives here. This is Mr. Thief.

97
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:25,600
Why? Why like this? He's not a thief,

98
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:30,680
he's between jobs.
-So who are you?

99
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:33,360
I have a feeling they're going to come through here,
checking house by house,

100
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:36,680
so for this purpose, if the police come to check,

101
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,560
I'm your friend.
-Friend?

102
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:42,880
Merav, that's only if the police show up.
-Then I'm going to take a shower.

103
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:46,480
No showering, sit here in the living room and be quiet.
-What, is this a kidnapping?

104
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,920
Sit here, I'm telling you.
-I'm sweating like crazy.

105
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,360
No way I'm staying in the living room like this.
-Sit!

106
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,640
What is that? What did you do?
-A tranquilizer dart.

107
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:57,960
What?
-It's just a tranquilizer dart.

108
00:05:58,040 --> 00:06:00,360
And she'll be okay?
-Yeah, she'll sleep for about ten minutes,

109
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:01,880
after that everything will be fine.

110
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:05,720
Where do you get something like that?

111
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:09,960
Okay, I'm going to call,
tell my parents Shabbat Shalom

112
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,360
and check that everything's okay.

113
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:15,520
Okay, everything's ready. Can we start?

114
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,560
This is the last time there are delays.

115
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:21,760
The schnitzels are getting cold! People are getting heated...

116
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:24,160
Okay. Enough, Rivka. I think the message got through.

117
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:26,920
It got through, but maybe it didn't register?

118
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:31,240
There are areas around the globe
where the reception is a bit problematic.

119
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:34,640
Speaking of problematic, where's Shabi?
-She's calling her parents

120
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,640
to check that nothing happened and to say Shabbat Shalom.

121
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,840
Can’t we wait until after dinner?

122
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:41,560
It's fine, she usually calls
before dinner, she doesn’t want them to wait.

123
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:44,120
Oh, so they don’t wait.

124
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,760
Okay, fine, we’ll wait.

125
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:48,840
Alone.

126
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,840
In the dark.
-Exactly.

127
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:52,080
Excuse me for a moment.

128
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:57,720
"Who loves Shabbat..."

129
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,640
Who's that from?

130
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:03,920
It's from Shai, our daughter.

131
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,400
Okay, you can answer normally,
no need for extra words.

132
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,440
And no sharp movements.

133
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,520
Put it on speaker.

134
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,240
Hello.
-Hey, Mom, what’s up?

135
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:21,800
Everything’s fine. And you?
-Everything’s good,

136
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:24,560
we’re here at the parents'. They’re waiting for me for Kiddush,

137
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:28,240
I called to wish you a Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom, Shabbat Shalom.

138
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:31,600
Is everything okay? Because when we drove here
we saw a lot of police cars

139
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,960
heading your way. Did something happen?

140
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:37,440
No, no. Everything’s fine here. It’s completely quiet.

141
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:41,120
Meirav, hang up.
-Okay. Alright, Mom, we’ll see you tomorrow.

142
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:44,280
Shai, there won’t be any mishap tomorrow.

143
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:47,080
What happened?
-Nothing happened.

144
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,600
Okay, so we’ll see you tomorrow.

145
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:52,720
And give my regards
to Shai.

146
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:56,800
And warm kisses to Riki.
-Okay.

147
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:57,960
Shabbat Shalom.
-Bye.

148
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,880
What happened?
-Very strange.

149
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,720
She sent kisses to your mom.

150
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,960
It must have slipped out. Regards and kisses go together.

151
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,920
No, that’s not all.
-Shai, do me a favor,

152
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,440
my mom is waiting alone, in the dark.

153
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:12,360
She also said there won’t be any mishap tomorrow.
-Why? Is she sick or something?

154
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:14,240
I don’t know. Shai, honey, it worries me,

155
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:17,200
but forget it, don’t make a big deal out of it,
your mom is already upset.

156
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:22,760
Does anyone have any arrangements
before we start Kiddush?

157
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:23,840
No, no, we can start.

158
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:28,520
"On the sixth day, the heavens and the earth
and all their hosts were finished..."

159
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:31,520
One-way street. Great.
He won’t be able to escape from here.

160
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:34,400
No problem.
-"Cigarettes," here "lighter,"

161
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:38,000
"Cigarettes," here "lighter."
I don’t want any smoke coming from the area.

162
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,919
Repeat, no smoke. There’s permission to open fire. End.

163
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:45,560
What happened here?

164
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:50,040
Mr. Thief, is she waking up?
-What was that?

165
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:53,200
He shot me with a tranquilizer dart.
-What?

166
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,840
How did you let him do that to me?

167
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,880
He took advantage of me? Dad, I’m your daughter.

168
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:02,840
What did he do to me? Did he touch me?
How did you let him, Dad?

169
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:05,720
What... you won’t tell me where to get something like that?

170
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,240
Who is it?

171
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:11,920
This is my daughter, Orna.
-You can answer.

172
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,800
Same procedure. No unnecessary words, speaker.

173
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:19,720
Hello.
-Hello, Mom, Shabbat Shalom.

174
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:22,840
What’s going on?
-Everything’s fine. Shabbat Shalom.

175
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:26,280
How’s Dad?
-Everything’s fine.

176
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:28,200
Great. Okay, see you tomorrow.

177
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:32,920
Orna, I didn’t arrange for mishap tomorrow.

178
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:35,560
What?
-So we’ll see you tomorrow.

179
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:38,640
Send my regards to Moshe

180
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:42,840
and warm kisses to his mom.
-Bye.

181
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,200
Because
"Yachin

182
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,160
Great.

183
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:47,800
Who's that?

184
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:50,920
That's my son, Manny.

185
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:54,760
Same procedure: no messing around, Shabbat Shalom, speaker.

186
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:56,880
Hello.
-Hello, Mom.

187
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:59,120
Hey, Shabbat Shalom.

188
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:02,280
How's it going?
-Everything's fine here.

189
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:04,960
I'm not doing any messing around tomorrow.
-What?

190
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:09,160
Send my regards to Alon and warm kisses to his mom.

191
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,600
Okay, bye.
-Bye.

192
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:15,040
Alright. So, who’s this now?

193
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:18,560
My daughter, Efrat.
-How many kids do you have? So...

194
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,040
Hello.
-Hello, Mom.

195
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,000
Efrat?

196
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,600
Yes.
-Shabbat Shalom.

197
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,560
Everything's fine here.

198
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,600
What, a lot of money?
-A lot.

199
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:34,920
Those who don’t know what to do with it.
-What do you mean?

200
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:39,120
For example, they have
a special and exotic dinner

201
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:42,720
with all sorts of fancy dishes.
-You know, I'm really worried.

202
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,560
What, because of the messing around tomorrow?
-Yeah.

203
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,400
I should be the one worried,
I was counting on the messing around.

204
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:48,320
She's a good girl, trust me,

205
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:52,080
so what are you eating at her exclusive dinner?

206
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:55,800
I know... I think you'll understand.

207
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Yuck.
-You don’t say yuck about food.

208
00:10:58,120 --> 00:11:00,080
You don’t call food yuck.
-It's really weird, I'm telling you.

209
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,960
Maybe something happened?
-Nothing happened,

210
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:04,080
I'm sure everything's fine.
She's probably just a bit tired. What...

211
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:06,680
I'm worried.
-So when do you need to leave?

212
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:10,600
Don’t be late. She’s from a family that
doesn’t like tardiness.

213
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,000
Turns out the dinner was canceled.

214
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:22,240
It's nice that all the kids are calling for Shabbat.

215
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:24,600
Yeah, we have good kids.

216
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:30,040
I was born in prison.
My parents are from two different prisons.

217
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,480
What a gut-wrenching story...

218
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:36,200
What did you do that everyone’s chasing you?
-I broke into the safari.

219
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:39,520
Who's that?
-That's my daughter, Shavi.

220
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:42,880
What, do you have so many kids
that you accidentally called two Shavi?

221
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,280
Same procedure.

222
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:52,720
Yeah, Shavi, what's up?
-Mom, are you guys mad at us about something?

223
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:55,480
No, God forbid.
-So everything's fine.

224
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:59,280
Everything's perfectly fine.
-So why isn’t there any messing around tomorrow?

225
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:01,640
Oh no.

226
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:06,200
Shavi, Dad and I are
watching an action movie on TV.

227
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,600
See you tomorrow and...

228
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:12,560
Yeah, and don’t... don’t forget kisses for Riki.

229
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,640
Okay.
-Shabbat Shalom.

230
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:18,440
Shabbat Shalom, Momma. Bye.
-So, everything's okay?

231
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:20,880
No, not at all. I can’t
figure out what's wrong with her.

232
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,560
What did she tell you?
-She’s not saying anything,

233
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:24,320
she says there’s no messing around tomorrow and that everything's fine.

234
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,360
That’s it, no explanations.
-Do you want me to call them?

235
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:28,000
No, I want to go there.

236
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,480
Now?
-Of course.

237
00:12:29,560 --> 00:12:31,720
But you can’t. What do you want,
for my mom to go on a barricade?

238
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:34,480
My dear, I don’t care if the barricade goes on a barricade.

239
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,440
My mom’s not feeling well.
I want to go check what's going on.

240
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:39,040
With what excuse?
-Just tell her the truth. What excuse?

241
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:41,560
Tell her they called and there's some
issue and she can't hear well,

242
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:43,080
We're going to check.
-What issue?

243
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:45,520
That we're faking tomorrow?
Come on, really, what can't she hear?

244
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:48,240
Oudi, tell her my mom sends her kisses.

245
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:51,160
Okay. That really doesn't sound good.
-Ah.

246
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:54,600
That's it, I'm not taking any more calls. Got it?

247
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:56,240
You said Shabbat Shalom to everyone.

248
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:58,240
Except for me, I didn't call.

249
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:00,440
But I'm already here, so there's no point in me calling.

250
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:02,520
I'm not calling and they're not calling.

251
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:05,280
I'm sure at this point
your parents are happy.

252
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,640
He's insulting me.

253
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:09,960
Leave it.

254
00:13:11,360 --> 00:13:13,920
Who is it?
-Police. Please open up.

255
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,600
Say "wait."
-Wait.

256
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:19,240
Remember, it's just a regular Friday
and I'm your daughter's boyfriend.

257
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:20,480
Open up.

258
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:25,200
Wait, what's your name?
-What does it matter now?

259
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:28,400
Ehud. Open up.
-Wait. Ehud what?

260
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:31,000
I don't know? Ben, Ehud Barak. Okay?

261
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:33,720
Come on, come on.
-And how long have we been together?

262
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,880
Is our relationship serious? Is it going somewhere?

263
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:39,040
I think it’ll be easier for me
to explain to the cop why you're sitting.

264
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,560
Please open up.

265
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,440
Good evening.
-Good evening.

266
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,560
Have you seen anyone suspicious hanging around here in the building?

267
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:52,720
No, no, not at all.

268
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:53,880
We didn't see anyone. No one.

269
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:57,240
Do you have something in your eye?
-No, my eyes are perfectly fine.

270
00:13:57,400 --> 00:14:00,280
Gentlemen, we're dealing with a cunning criminal,

271
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:03,920
very dangerous and low-life,
who has broken in several times

272
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:07,280
to the safari in Ramat Gan and stolen exotic animals.

273
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:10,440
We... we trust you, the police.

274
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:15,000
We trust your sharp instincts.

275
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:18,600
This is my new boyfriend,
he just came to meet the parents.

276
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:22,280
Ehud. But I call him Oudi.

277
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:25,120
We're getting married in the fall.

278
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,400
Good evening.
-Good evening to you too.

279
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:29,680
Well, sorry for interrupting,
have a nice and quiet rest of Shabbat

280
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:33,240
and if you see anything suspicious, call 100.

281
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,240
There's no doubt we'll call.

282
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:37,640
And good thing too.
-Thanks.

283
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,320
I told you the news
would worry even your mom.

284
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:44,400
I think you're just being hysterical. It's nothing, no faking.

285
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,200
It's not the faking, idiot.

286
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,200
Why are you calling me an idiot?
-Because you're an idiot.

287
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:50,720
What idiot? Friday night, my mom's freaking out,

288
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:54,080
and you're taking me to your mom's
just because she said there's no faking tomorrow?

289
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:55,960
What, does that seem normal?
Like, like

290
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:58,360
the fact that your mom's freaking out
seems totally normal to me.

291
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,920
Look at that, they're really
sending more forces over there.

292
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,360
Really, maybe something happened?
-I think there's a checkpoint there.

293
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:06,240
Maybe it's a terrorist on the run.
-They would have announced it on the radio.

294
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,560
Come on, and they didn't announce anything.

295
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,120
On the other hand, they should have announced
that there's no faking tomorrow too.

296
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,480
On the third hand, they should have announced that you're an idiot.

297
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:20,000
Did you see how naturally you told the cop
that you're my new boyfriend?

298
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,880
Meirav, you wouldn't really want to
be in a long-term relationship

299
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:25,000
with some prisoner or criminal.

300
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,840
No,
not that I think you're a criminal. Yeah.

301
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:30,040
In some cases, it can even be good.

302
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:34,400
He's in jail, you're at home,
no fights, no headaches.

303
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:37,520
I get that your wife gives you a lot of headaches. Huh?

304
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:39,600
No, no. You didn't understand what I said.

305
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,480
I was speaking in metaphors.

306
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:46,360
I always dreamed of being a hostage of a kidnapper like you.

307
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:49,800
Pinch me, babe.
-Hey, have you ever heard of "Stockholm Syndrome"?

308
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:52,040
What, what do you want?
-Stockholm Syndrome.

309
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:56,280
It's a syndrome where the hostage falls in love
or, in our case, falls in love with the kidnapper.

310
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,240
All she wants is for him to kidnap her!

311
00:15:58,320 --> 00:15:59,920
For an unforgettable experience.

312
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,520
Do you want me to help you make a better meal here?

313
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:05,280
I don't know where you're getting
this syndrome from,

314
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:08,120
but from now on, be quiet.
-Fine.

315
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,760
He's definitely hiding here! Someone missed them.

316
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:14,560
Listen, the police chief is on his way
and his daughter loves the safari.

317
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,360
I need to give him smarter answers.

318
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:20,360
He's "connecting" on the way
or "matzot."
And closing <i>y</i> like

319
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:23,120
I want you to find that dirty ashtray
at all costs.

320
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:24,680
What’s going on? Why is there a police command center here?

321
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:27,160
Wow, wow, wow.
You can't enter. This is a crime scene.

322
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:29,400
What do you mean? You're blocking
the way to my parents' house.

323
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:31,680
I need to do laundry.
-You can't go in.

324
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,640
There's suspicion that the escaped criminal entered this building.

325
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,640
Escaped criminal? Armed?

326
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,480
We don't know too many details,

327
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:39,040
but we don't want to take unnecessary risks,

328
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:42,240
if you know what I mean.
-Of course I understand, I'm not stupid.

329
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:43,960
I got it too.

330
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,400
Look, she's not answering.
-She's not answering?

331
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:47,400
My mom isn't answering.

332
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,320
What’s this? What are you doing here?
-We called to say Shabbat Shalom,

333
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,240
Mom said there's no meziluf tomorrow.
It seemed strange, so we came.

334
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,440
She told us there's no meziluf either.

335
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:55,880
Hey, Orna, Moshe, and Shai,
what's going on here? Why is there police?

336
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:57,920
Mom told everyone there's no meziluf tomorrow. Did she tell you too?

337
00:16:58,280 --> 00:16:59,920
Yeah, that's why we came.
-There's a criminal in the building.

338
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,920
Excuse me, are you all from the same family?
-Yeah.

339
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,880
And you all came because of the meziluf?
-Yeah!

340
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,359
Meziluf is a type of food.

341
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:08,680
Really great detective. Awesome.

342
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:11,640
All the cigarettes burning in the area,

343
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:14,839
has anyone of you come across... meziluf?

344
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:17,480
Sir, the tracker... the detective,
it's not meziluf day, it's tomorrow.

345
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:19,480
Usually, there's one every Saturday, and she told us there isn't,

346
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:21,319
so that's suspicious.
-What’s suspicious or not suspicious

347
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:24,520
is my job. Okay? I have an idea.

348
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:25,680
I need a volunteer.

349
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,280
Moshe... Moshe, move.

350
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,680
Tell me, have you heard dogs?

351
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,200
Yes or no?

352
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:39,600
You said to be quiet, so we're quiet.
-Okay, now we can talk.

353
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:42,680
Yes or no?
-It's the neighbor's dog, Gliksman.

354
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:45,360
Gliksman is the neighbor, not the dog.

355
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:48,120
They went away for the weekend,
and I promised to feed the dog,

356
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:50,160
so he's probably hungry.
-I'm hungry too.

357
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,920
Maybe you can let us do a kiddush, for heaven's sake.

358
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,720
Alright, hide the microphones
and set up two cameras for you,

359
00:17:56,120 --> 00:17:57,120
in case one breaks.

360
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:01,080
Babe, you don't have to do this.
-I always dreamed of being a cop.

361
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,000
Ready to go live.

362
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,360
I feel a bit clumsy with all the...

363
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:10,160
These microphones and cameras.
Kind of like Channel One.

364
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:13,040
I hope the sound quality
and the response will be better.

365
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:15,760
Me too.
-Alright, let’s go. Good luck.

366
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:18,560
Just remember, you’re only
our eyes and ears out there.

367
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:21,040
Don’t do anything stupid
like trying to take him down yourself.

368
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:23,040
Of course not! What am I, an idiot?

369
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:27,640
I haven’t really had a chance to do Kiddush at my place.

370
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:31,400
I’ve always dreamed of family and Kiddush,
that Friday night vibe.

371
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:34,600
I never really got to experience it.
-That’s really sad.

372
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,680
Well, here you go, now you get to.

373
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,640
You’ll hear Kiddush and eat proper food.

374
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,360
See? You’ll get used to
loving my parents.

375
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:43,280
Meirav... Kiddush.

376
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:48,560
"On the sixth day, the heavens and the earth

377
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:50,360
and all their hosts were finished."

378
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:52,920
Same procedure.

379
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,000
Who is it?
-It’s me, Shai.

380
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:59,440
Shai?
-Shai is my son. His.

381
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:02,400
Another one? Open gently.

382
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:03,640
If not, I’ll blow everything up.

383
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,280
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

384
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:11,880
Son... his.
-Shabbat Shalom.

385
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:16,040
Dad, Mom, Shabbat Shalom.

386
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:17,520
Sister.

387
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:19,920
You see, everything’s fine there.
-Yeah, and who’s that?

388
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,440
That’s the sister’s fiancé, right?

389
00:19:21,520 --> 00:19:23,840
Meet my new boyfriend, Ehud Barak.

390
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:25,760
Which Ehud <i>Barak...</i> is it, Ehud Barak.

391
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:28,120
Move
the
9)
Shvu
/שׁן. 'י'

392
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:31,080
Is he dangerous?
-Not more than the stuff we found in his car.

393
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:32,320
Get it?

394
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:34,440
Adam!

395
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:37,200
Everything will be fine if we act wisely.
-That’s what worries me.

396
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:39,640
Does anyone know why he chose
to come to Mom and Dad’s place?

397
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:43,080
Maybe because of the food.
-The food smells amazing.

398
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:46,480
Yeah. Can we please have Kiddush?
-Yes, yes, yes.

399
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:54,440
"On the sixth day, the heavens and the earth

400
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:58,600
and all...
-Cut it short.

401
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,520
Sabri Maranan-
-L'Chaim!

402
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:03,080
What’s that? What did you shoot me with?

403
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:05,040
Don’t worry, it’s a tranquilizer dart.

404
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,560
It wakes me up.

405
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:13,320
That’s it, let’s go, he’s neutralized.
Get into the apartment and stop him.

406
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:14,880
It wakes me up.
-Oh my God...

407
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,920
My eyes are shaking from him.

408
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,320
Kudos to your husband. Now I just hope

409
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:21,120
I can break this suspect during the interrogation

410
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,400
and find out where and to whom this was meant.

411
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:27,440
Don’t hurt him. He’s not that much of a monster.

412
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:29,720
I have a feeling I have some very exclusive and exotic info for you.

413
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:32,840
Where is he?

414
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:35,520
Honey, honey, are you okay?

415
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,680
He’s sleeping. Sleeping-
shnann, how I worried.

416
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:41,160
Did you set off a false alarm for them, huh?

417
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:43,640
False alarm red!

418
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,520
And for all those who were worried, there’s a false alarm tomorrow.
-And!

419
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:51,560
Alright, now that everyone’s here, let’s do Kiddush.

420
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:55,080
טוב, עכשיו, כשכולם כאן, אנחנו נעשה קידוש.

421
00:20:55,720 --> 00:21:02,200
"It's Friday, and the heavens and the earth..."

422
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:04,040
Dad, you've done this already.
-Oh, really?

423
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,440
Boy Royal
Mo.
(House
n
e

424
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:06,360
Sabri Maranan.

425
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:10,600
"Sabri Maranan."
-Cheers!

426
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:11,760
Where is he?

427
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:18,880
Honestly, I think the Israeli police
lost a model officer.

428
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:22,360
Wow, babe, how did you handle him? What a waste of time.

429
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:23,960
What’s this? They say you broke his rib.

430
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:27,080
I think I deserve an apology for the "idiot."

431
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:29,680
Honestly, yes. You're really a hero,

432
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:31,960
I'm sorry, and I love you.

433
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:36,520
Hello, Mom.
-Shame on you, you and your bride,

434
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:40,040
for getting up and leaving in the middle of a meal.

435
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:46,440
You left the kids
alone here, in the dark, in such a catastrophic situation.

436
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:48,520
What was so urgent?

437
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:51,480
Mom, I'll tell you later what happened.
-Is someone dead?

438
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:54,320
No.
-Then I'm not obligated to listen.

439
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:57,200
This is not how a son who loves his mom behaves.

440
00:21:57,280 --> 00:22:01,320
This is how an idiot behaves.
-It's chasing you.

441
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:03,000
We're almost there.

442
00:22:04,560 --> 00:22:07,320
You know that if we went this week
to both your mom's and my mom's,

443
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:09,040
then next week we have a free Friday.

444
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:11,040
You think so?

445
00:22:11,520 --> 00:22:12,360
Idiot.

446
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:17,240
I'm warning you! I told you to be careful. Be careful.

447
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:22,200
District Sh.
-Very funny.

448
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:23,400
What, you’re insulting me, babe?

449
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:25,240
Soon I'll stop you for insulting a public servant.

450
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:27,760
Right, what, you’re insulting me, babe?
-Just a little.

451
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:31,320
Mom called, said...

452
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:35,600
Good morning.

453
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,000
Excuse me.

454
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:45,520
Are you asking something?
-No.

455
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:46,800
Excuse me.

456
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:48,400
Who is this?

457
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:51,320
This is the sister's fiancé, right? Ehud Barak.

458
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:53,280
One more time without the sneeze.

459
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:57,960
She says there’s supposedly no mishap tomorrow
and everything is fine, no explanations.

460
00:22:58,440 --> 00:22:59,880
What did she tell you?
-That's what she said,

461
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:02,600
what you said last time, in the last line.

462
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,320
What an idiot I am.

